<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!--
    Empty entitlements = minimum-privilege hardened runtime.

    Apple notarization requires hardened runtime (`codesign --options runtime`).
    Tauri's macOS bundler invokes codesign with this file when
    `bundle.macOS.entitlements` is set, so an empty <dict/> opts the app into
    hardened runtime + library validation + DYLD-env-var protection without
    granting any additional capabilities.

    DO NOT add `com.apple.security.app-sandbox` here — it would break
    ScreenCaptureKit (the Screen Recording TCC prompt requires unsandboxed
    access to the system-wide capture API used in capture/macos.rs and
    macos_window.m) and would also break history writes outside the sandbox
    container.

    DO NOT add `com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit` or
    `com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory` — Tauri 2 uses
    WKWebView (JIT lives in Apple's already-entitled WebContent helper); the
    main process is native code with no JIT.

    DO NOT add `com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation` — Cargo.toml
    links only system frameworks; no third-party dylibs are loaded.

    Add entitlements here only with concrete justification.
  -->
</dict>
</plist>
